<br>
The things you have to watch out for when clearing to the boss mobs is that when there is multiple mobs pulled, and you try and CH a tank too early, you will usually die dued to agro.  If there's AE mobs pulled, you have to have better resist than your regular exp group.  You need to learn where are spots that you can hide.   <br>
Other things that you need to do different in a raid than an exp group is sometimes the tank in your group isn't getting hit, so you need to assist the mob to help out with heals.  You need to CH a lot earlier than exp mobs as well :P<br>
<br>
Now ontop the uber mobs, you may be put in a ch rotation.  Ch rotations are pretty simple, you pretty much just have to pay attention.  You may be assigned as a spot healer, you can pretty much just heal the tank whenever you see his HP drop.  <br>
<br>
One final thing that you want to know is that you may have a lot of lag in raids.  If this is a problem you will need to fix it because you can't heal for shit with lag in a raid.<br>
