<br>
On a raid you should be clicking around a lot to see who needs health.  Not all groups will have a cleric and not all groups will even have a healer.  Paying attention to &quot;You will not evade me (Abouttodie)&quot; will also tell you who might need a spot heal.<br>
<br>
That is, until you get to the big encounter--as Meugly has said.  Then you may get into a healing rotation.  Either you have a hard and fast hotkey, where you heal, pause, say a little message, like, &quot;Healing Main Tank, next cleric.&quot;, or you just watch for the Cheal messages and do your duty to keep him/her alive.<br>
<br>
Just remeber you role in the raid is to keep people alive.. and sometimes not your own group--usually a designated tank or two (know you tank rotation).<br>
<br>
Your role is not to keep everyone at full health, nor to get XP, nor to make the fight go faster by spending all your time landing Mark of Retribution.<br>
<br>
What is different is that you may not even have to keep *your* group alive.  You may be sole-ly concerned with keeping a single tank so the *rest* of the raid does not die.<br>
<br>
That's about my 2c<br>
<br>
